-# Trade-off vs the canonical docker-compose.yml at the repo root:
-#   * Slower first start (~90s for clone + pip install)
-#   * Slower restart (same, because we re-clone for `latest`)
-#   * Self-contained: no separate build pipeline needed
-#
-# For production with frequent deploys, consider building an image
-# via GitHub Actions and publishing to GHCR; this file is for the
-# fastest possible time-to-deploy on a fresh Hostinger Docker Manager.
-#
-# Environment variables — supply them via Hostinger Settings ->
-# Environment Variables on this Docker project. None are required for
-# the system to boot; missing variables degrade specific subsystems:
-#   OPENAI_API_KEY     LLM disabled, mechanical-only
-#   OANDA_API_TOKEN    PaperBroker, no live trading
-#   OANDA_ACCOUNT_ID   PaperBroker, no live trading
